This document is for test cases for the Book Challenge page.

Test case #1: Function of setting a number of books the user want to read

Steps:
1) Navigate to the Library page, ensure one book is ticked "Read?"
2) Add a number 9 to the blank box in the sentence "I want to read __ books"
3) Click the "Update" button

- Expected result: 
    - In the sentence "You have read __ of __ books" where both "__" contain a number, 
    the first number should be 1; the second number should be 9.
    - "11%" should appear at the end of progress bar
    - 11% of progress bar should be in green color, while the rest of the bar is white
- Actual result: Same as expected result.
- Pass/Fail: Pass

---------------------------------------------------

Test case #2: Setting a massive number as number of books the user want to read

Steps:
1) Add number 10000000000 to the blank box in the sentence "I want to read __ books"
2) Click the "Update" button

- Expected result: Message "Enter number between 1 and 100" should appear.
- Actual result: In the sentence "You have read __ of __ books" where both "__" contain a number, 
    the second number is 10000000000.
- Pass/Fail: Fail

